  "text": "The k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object import chain traces through the Kubernetes codebase as follows:\n\n## Core Runtime Interface\nThe `runtime.Object` interface is defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/interfaces.go` (line 336-339) and requires all API types to implement two methods:\n1. `GetObjectKind() schema.ObjectKind`\n2. `DeepCopyObject() Object`\n\nThe interface is documented in the same file with extensive explanation (lines 332-335) noting that all API types registered with a Scheme must support this interface.\n\n## TypeMeta and RawExtension\nIn `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/types.go`, the foundational `TypeMeta` struct (lines 38-43) is defined with fields for APIVersion and Kind. This file also defines `RawExtension` (lines 103-111) which holds raw serialized data and implements the `runtime.Object` interface for handling unknown types.\n\n## Metav1 Type Definitions\nIn `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/types.go`, metav1 redefines `TypeMeta` (lines 42-57) and introduces `ObjectMeta` (lines 109+) which contains standard Kubernetes object metadata like Name, Namespace, UID, and Labels. These types form the foundation for implementing runtime.Object.\n\n## Core/v1 API Types\nAll types in `staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go` that implement runtime.Object do so by embedding both `metav1.TypeMeta` (for kind/apiVersion) and `metav1.ObjectMeta` (for name/namespace/uid). Examples include:\n- Pod (line 5012-5017): Embeds TypeMeta and ObjectMeta\n- Service (line 5773-5778): Embeds TypeMeta and ObjectMeta\n- Node, Namespace, Secret, ConfigMap, Event, ReplicationController, and all other core/v1 resources follow the same pattern\n\n## Registration Mechanism\nIn `staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/register.go` (lines 45-99), the `addKnownTypes()` function registers all core/v1 types into the Scheme:\n- It calls `scheme.AddKnownTypes(SchemeGroupVersion, &Pod{}, &PodList{}, &Service{}, &ServiceList{}, etc.)`\n- This is wrapped by `SchemeBuilder` and `AddToScheme` to register the types\n\nThe registration chain flows through:\n1. `addKnownTypes()` in core/v1/register.go - registers all core/v1 types\n2. `metav1.AddToGroupVersion()` in staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/register.go (lines 66-86) - registers metav1 types like WatchEvent and Status\n3. Ultimately calls into `Scheme.AddKnownTypes()` in staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/scheme.go\n\n## DeepCopyObject Implementation\nThe `DeepCopyObject()` method required by runtime.Object is auto-generated in `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` for metav1 types, and similar generated files exist for all core/v1 types.\n\n## Import Chain Summary\n- Core API types import metav1 types from k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\n- metav1 types import runtime types from k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\n- The registration system connects all these types to the Scheme for serialization and deserialization\n- All core/v1 resources in `staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/` implement runtime.Object through the TypeMeta and ObjectMeta embedding pattern\n"
